# Commit message after changes

Whenever you **modify project files** (code, config, tests, docs in this repo), end your reply with a short section:

**Commit message:** `…`

Use one line in [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) style when it fits, e.g. `fix(spec): quote symbol for RuboCop`, `feat(header): relocate AI summarize control`. If the change is mixed, use a clear imperative subject (~72 chars).

If there were **no file edits** in the turn, omit the commit message block.
